.:: Zebra puzzle ::.
5 different games are played: backgammon, bridge, mah-jongg, go, billiard
There are 5 different nationalities: english, spanish, ukranian, norwegian, japanese
The people prefer 5 different types of sport: volleyball, ice-hockey, cricket, snowboarding, lacrosse
There are 5 different favourite beverages: coffee, tea, milk, orange-juice, water
The people's birthday is in 5 different months: september, january, february, april, may

1. the english is the person playing backgammon
2. the spanish is the person who's birthday is in september
3. the person drinking coffee is the person playing bridge
4. the ukranian is the person drinking tea
5. the person playing bridge is to the right of the person playing mah-jongg
6. the person who's sport is volleyball is the person who's birthday is in may
7. the person who's sport is ice-hockey is the person playing go
8. the person drinking milk is in the middle
9. the norwegian is on the far left
10. the person who's sport is cricket is on the left or right of the person who's birthday is in january
11. the person who's sport is ice-hockey is to the left or right of the person who's birthday is in april
12. the person who's sport is snowboarding is the person drinking orange-juice
13. the japanese is the person who's sport is lacrosse
14. the norwegian is to the left or right of the person playing billiard

.:: Answer ::.
